# Fluff Date: 2026-02-28 16:30:01
<overview>
<p>The Vanir is an assault DropShip designed during the Jihad for Clan Ghost Bear, serving as the missile defense counterpart to its sister design, the Aesir fighter carrier. Together, the two classes were designed to provide escort protection for convoys and the Clan's surviving WarShip assets following devastating engagements with Word of Blake naval forces. First operational in 3077, the class was primarily tasked as a fleet defender using its extensive missile batteries. The design has remained in limited production as a key component of the Rasalhague Dominion's naval forces.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>The Vanir is an 18,000-ton military spheroid assault DropShip optimized for fleet missile defense. Its primary armament consists of extensive Piranha and Stingray sub-capital missile launcher batteries, providing layered missile defense coverage that can intercept incoming ordnance and engage hostile vessels at range. This sub-capital arsenal is supplemented by HAG 40 autocannons, ATM 12 launchers, ER Large Lasers, and Large Pulse Lasers for engaging conventional targets. Thirty anti-missile systems provide comprehensive point defense. Ninety tons of Ferro-Aluminum armor gives the Vanir substantial survivability, concentrated on the arcs most likely to face incoming fire during defensive operations. The drive system provides respectable acceleration, allowing the Vanir to maintain escort position with most fleet formations. A complement of Elemental marines provides boarding capability when required. The Vanir's design philosophy emphasizes defensive screening over offensive power projection, making it most effective when operating in concert with the Aesir carrier or other offensive-oriented vessels that can exploit the defensive umbrella the Vanir provides.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The standard Vanir serves in its baseline fleet defender configuration, providing missile defense and escort capability for Clan Ghost Bear naval formations. These vessels typically pair with Aesir carriers, combining defensive missile screening with offensive fighter capability to create a complementary escort package for convoys and high-value WarShip assets.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Vanir was developed alongside the Aesir as Clan Ghost Bear's response to the devastating naval losses inflicted by Word of Blake forces during the Jihad. Ghost Bear naval planners recognized that replacing their lost WarShips was impossible in the near term, and instead developed the Vanir and Aesir as a cost-effective paired escort solution that could protect remaining fleet assets and vital supply convoys from Blakist naval raiders.</p><p>Production began in 3077 at two facilities: the primary line at Alshain Naval Yards and a secondary line at Gorton, Kingsley and Thorpe Enterprises on Rasalhague. The Vanir saw its first combat deployments in the final years of the Jihad, where its missile batteries proved effective at deterring attacks on Ghost Bear convoys. Prior to the Liberation of Terra, some Vanirs were gifted to Clan Nova Cat as part of a secret agreement between the Bears and Allied Coalition leader Devlin Stone. These vessels were drawn from the heavy escort forces protecting the Leviathan-class Heavy Battleship Great Bear, which was subsequently lost during the liberation in 3078, sowing lasting resentment among the Ghost Bear people.</p><p>After the war, Jihad-induced production at the Gorton, Kingsley and Thorpe facility on Rasalhague was scheduled to cease around 3080, with remaining hulls sent to Alshain Naval Yards for final assembly. Economic considerations prompted the Ghost Bears to consolidate production and simplify their logistics. The class remained in limited service with the Rasalhague Dominion's touman, with few examples seen outside Ghost Bear formations. The Vanir's specialized defensive role and Clan-tech construction made it a closely guarded asset not readily available to outside buyers.</p>
</history>

